LAST UPDATE: 2015/10/16

- Install OPAM and OCaml 4.02
    - We need ocamlc.opt for apron.20150518
- Install m4 (for apron and MoCHi).
- Install libgmp-dev and libmpfr-dev (for apron).
- Install apron by OPAM.
- Add an opam repositry by the following command (for Z3).
    $ opam remote add termite https://github.com/termite-analyser/opam-termite.git
- Install Z3 by OPAM.
- Install autoconf (for FPAT and MoCHi).
- Install extlib by OPAM (for FPAT and MoCHi).
- Install camlp5 by OPAM (for FPAT).
- Install FPAT by the following command
    $ autoconf
    $ ./configure --disable-csisat --disable-minisat
    $ make install-lib
    $ make
    $ make install
- Install ocamlgraph by OPAM (for MoCHi).
- Compile MoCHi by the following command
    $ aclocal -I m4
    $ autoconf
    $ ./configure
    $ make
- You can find the MoCHi executable "mochi.opt"


# Here is an example of a list of commands for installing MoCHi on Ubuntu 15.04.
# We assume that TRecS & HorSat are found in $PATH
apt-get install opam m4 libgmp-dev libmpfr-dev autoconf
opam init
opam update
opam switch 4.02.3
opam remote add termite https://github.com/termite-analyser/opam-termite.git
opam install apron.20150518 Z3 camlp5 extlib
git clone git@bitbucket.org:uhiro/vhorn.git fpat
cd fpat
autoconf
./configure --disable-csisat --disable-minisat
cd ..
wget http://www.cs.nyu.edu/acsys/cvc3/releases/2.4.1/linux64/cvc3-2.4.1-optimized-static.tar.gz
tar xvzf cvc3-2.4.1-optimized-static.tar.gz
git clone git@bitbucket.org:ryosu_sato/mochi.git
cp cvc3-2.4.1-optimized-static/bin/cvc3 mochi
cd mochi
aclocal -I m4
autoconf
./configure
make
ls -l mochi.opt
